6. Example Splunk-style detection queries
Mass deletion
index=windows sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode IN (4660,4663)
ObjectName="D:\\Shares\\*"
AccessMask IN ("0x10000","%%1537")
| bucket _time span=10m
| stats count dc(ObjectName) as unique_files by _time, SubjectUserName, Computer
| where count > 100 OR unique_files > 100
Permission change
index=windows sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=4670
ObjectName="D:\\Shares\\*"
| table _time Computer SubjectUserName ObjectName ProcessName
Access to admin shares
index=windows sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode IN (5140,5145)
ShareName IN ("\\\\*\\C$","\\\\*\\D$","\\\\*\\ADMIN$")
| table _time Computer SubjectUserName IpAddress ShareName RelativeTargetName
File share access outside business hours
index=windows sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode IN (4663,5140,5145)
ObjectName="D:\\Shares\\*"
| eval hour=strftime(_time,"%H")
| where hour < 7 OR hour > 19
| stats count by SubjectUserName, Computer, ObjectName, hour
7. Example Microsoft Sentinel KQL queries
Mass file deletion
SecurityEvent
| where EventID in (4660, 4663)
| where ObjectName startswith @"D:\Shares\"
| summarize FileCount=count(), UniqueFiles=dcount(ObjectName)
    by Account, Computer, bin(TimeGenerated, 10m)
| where FileCount > 100 or UniqueFiles > 100
Permission change on shared folder
SecurityEvent
| where EventID == 4670
| where ObjectName startswith @"D:\Shares\"
| project TimeGenerated, Computer, Account, ObjectName, ProcessName, Activity
Admin share access
SecurityEvent
| where EventID in (5140, 5145)
| where ShareName has_any ("C$", "D$", "ADMIN$")
| project TimeGenerated, Computer, Account, ShareName, IpAddress, RelativeTargetName
Failed access attempts
SecurityEvent
| where EventID in (4656, 4663, 5145)
| where EventData has "Access Denied"
| summarize FailedAttempts=count()
    by Account, Computer, IpAddress, bin(TimeGenerated, 10m)
| where FailedAttempts > 20
8. Recommended alert thresholds

Start with baseline thresholds, then tune them.

Use Case	Initial Threshold
Mass deletion	More than 100 deletes in 10 minutes
Mass modification	More than 500 writes/modifications in 10 minutes
Permission change	Any change on sensitive share
Failed access	More than 20 failures in 10 minutes
Sensitive share access	Any unauthorized user
Large read activity	More than 1,000 file reads in 30 minutes
Admin share access	Any non-admin access
Audit log cleared	Any occurrence
Service account interactive logon	Any occurrence
Out-of-hours sensitive access	More than 50 accesses or any permission/delete action
