7. Example alert format

For each monitoring use case, document it like this:

Use Case Name:
SQL Sysadmin Role Granted

Objective:
Detect unauthorized privilege escalation in SQL Server.

Data Sources:
SQL Server Audit Logs
Windows Security Logs

Detection Logic:
Trigger alert when any login or user is added to the sysadmin fixed server role.

Severity:
Critical

MITRE Mapping:
Privilege Escalation

Response:
1. Validate whether this was part of approved change.
2. Identify who made the change.
3. Check source host and login time.
4. Review recent activity by the modified account.
5. Remove privilege if unauthorized.
6. Raise security incident if suspicious.
